    array(
      'title' => 'Promotion of domestic products of Tajikistan through Geographical Indications - reinforcing the relationship between people, place and products.',
      'image' => 'image_9.jpg',
      'description' => 'A national technical working group was established under the Government\'s Export Agency Of the Republic of Tajikistan for the determination of geographical indications of products. This working group was created at the initiative of the Export Agency, relevant ministries and departments, the private sector and international industry organizations in accordance with the instruction of the Government of the Republic of Tajikistan. The first meeting of this working group on April 28, 2020 was opened with opening remarks by the Director Export Agencies. In his speech, he noted that the Government of the Republic of Tajikistan pays special attention to product promotion and strengthening of the country\'s export potential, and therefore supported the initiative to establish a National Technical Working Group on Export Promotion and Identification geographical indications. During the meeting, Rakhimzoda Bahodur, Deputy Director of the Export Agency, informed the participants about the main goals and objectives of the Working Group and said that its members should first develop a list of potential products and discuss it with representatives from groups and industry associations. He added that representatives of the scientific community, including industry scientists, should be involved in the process of determining the specificity and special quality characteristics of the selected products with the purpose of preparing the evidence base for the development of their feasibility study. Participants discussed and supported the form, potential products and future activities of the Working Group within the CANDY-V project, which is being implemented by the European Union program in Central Asia (stage 5). AT currently, weekly training courses are held in the form of webinars with the participation of foreign experts. The Export Agency under the Government of the Republic of Tajikistan will carry out activities this Working Group and ongoing activities involving a number of representatives from relevant ministries and departments, the private sector (manufacturers, processors, exporters, industry associations, etc.).',
